text: Greene County is a county in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, the population was 13,530. The county seat is Leakesville. The county was founded in 1811 and is named after American Revolutionary War General Nathanael Greene. == References == Category:1810s establishments in Mississippi Territory Category:1811 establishments in the United States Category:Mississippi counties
title: Greene County, Mississippi
